-- Used NodeJS, Express web framework
-- Used mongoose as a ORM to communicate with MongoDB database
-- Used the proper HTTP verbs to make it RESTful (GET, POST and DELETE)
-- Return JSON data

 >> Prerequisites 

	1.Install NodeJS
		with dependencies
		"dependencies": {
		    "body-parser": "~1.12.4",
		    "cookie-parser": "~1.3.5",
		    "debug": "~2.2.0",
		    "express": "~4.12.4",
		    "jade": "~1.9.2",
		    "morgan": "~1.5.3",
		    "serve-favicon": "~2.2.1",
		    "mongodb": "~2.0.33",
		    "monk": "~1.0.1",
		    "mongoose": "~3.6.13"
		}
	2.Install MongoDB



open command propmt or terminal

1. run command $ /birds npm install to install all dependencies, (ALL THE REQUIREDor dependencies's MODULES YOU CAN FIND IN 'node_modules' folder)

2. $ node app.js

Server will start and listen on port 8080. (if you want to change the port number, change the value of port variable in app.js)

-- Tested all the APIs using Postman plugin.


